select.description: returns a list with all the elements descending from elt whose CSS selector matches S

select_one.description: returns the elements matching the specified CSS selector, otherwise None

abs_left.description: position of the element relatively to the window left border

abs_top.description: position of the element relatively to the window top border

children.description: the element's children in the document tree

clear.description: removes all the descendants of the element

closest.description: removes all the descendants of the element

index.description: elt.index([selector]) returns the index (an integer) of the element among its parent's children. If selector is specified, only the elements matching the CSS selector are taken into account ; in this case, if no element matches, the method returns -1.

inside.description: elt.inside(other) tests if elt is contained inside element other

left.description: the position of the element relatively to the left border of the first positioned parent (1)

top.description: the position of the element relatively to the upper border of the first positioned parent (1)

html.description: the HTML code inside the element

options.description: access to an option by its index : option = elt.options[index]

options_insert.description: insertion of an option at the index position : elt.options.insert(index,option)

options_append.description: insertion of an option at the index position : elt.options.insert(index,option)

bubbles.description: boolean, indicates whether the given event bubbles up through the DOM or not

cancelable.description: boolean, indicates whether the event is cancelable or not

currentTarget.description: instance of DOMNode ; identifies the current target for the event, as the event traverses the DOM. It always refers to the element the event handler has been attached to as opposed to event.target which identifies the element on which the event occurred.

defaultPrevented.description: boolean indicating whether or not event.preventDefault() was called on the event

eventPhase.description: integer, indicates which phase of the event flow is currently being evaluated

target.description: DOMNode instance ; the object the event was dispatched on. It is different than event.currentTarget when the event handler is called in bubbling or capturing phase of the event

timeStamp.description: integer, the time (in milliseconds since Jan. 1st, 1970 at 0h) at which the event was created

preventDefault.description: prevents the execution of the action associated by default to the event

stopPropagation.description: prevents further propagation of the current event

altKey.description: Returns whether the 'ALT' key was pressed when the mouse event was triggered

button.description: Returns which mouse button was pressed when the mouse event was triggered

buttons.description: Returns which mouse buttons were pressed when the mouse event was triggered

clientX.description: Returns the horizontal coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the current window, when the mouse event was triggered

clientY.description: Returns the vertical coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the current window, when the mouse event was triggered

ctrlKey.description: Returns whether the 'CTRL' key was pressed when the mouse event was triggered

detail.description: Returns a number that indicates how many times the mouse was clicked

metaKey.description: Returns whether the 'META' key was pressed when an event was triggered

pageX.description: Returns the horizontal coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the document, when the mouse event was triggered

pageY.description: Returns the vertical coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the document, when the mouse event was triggered

relatedTarget.description: Returns the element related to the element that triggered the mouse event

screenX.description: Returns the horizontal coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the screen, when an event was triggered

screenY.description: Returns the vertical coordinate of the mouse pointer, relative to the screen, when an event was triggered

shiftKey.description: Returns whether the 'SHIFT' key was pressed when an event was triggered

which.description: Returns which mouse button was pressed when the mouse event was triggered

charCode.description: Returns the Unicode character code of the key that triggered the onkeypress event

key.description: Returns the key value of the key represented by the event

keyCode.description: Returns the Unicode character code of the key that triggered the onkeypress event, or the Unicode key code of the key that triggered the onkeydown or onkeyup event

location.description: Returns the location of a key on the keyboard or device

dataTransfer.description: Creates and returns a new DataTransfer object.
